oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Bricks Falling, Masonic Building Collapse, 1949
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the Masonic Building in downtown Clarksville as the side of the building starts to crumble. A crowd watches as bricks fall from a widening crack in the side of the building and the front of the building is starting to buckle.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Building failures; Freemasonry--Lodges; Building, Brick; Advertising; Crowds;
